President Cyril Ramaphosa. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - All eyes are on President Cyril Ramaphosa as he's expected to address the country this evening. Ramaphosa held a consultation with the National Coronavirus Command Council this weekend. Last week the country officially entered the second wave of the COVID-19 pandemic. South Africa's total cases now stand at almost 861,000. One-hundred and seventy more people have died from the virus. Cumulative deaths are at just over 23,000. More than 761,000 people have recovered and nearly 6-million tests have been conducted.